content:
Every protected route on the Fastify API uses a preHandler to check permissions before the request reaches the handler. Example:

```js
// Require authentication only
{ preHandler: app.requireAuth }

// Require a specific permission
{ preHandler: app.requirePermission('agile_milestones', 'create') }
```

If a user lacks the required permission, the API returns 403 Forbidden before any database access occurs. Permissions are loaded from the database at login time and attached to the session — they are not re-checked on every request.
